<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Obviously I=E2=80=99ll miss this but at least =
it is going to go <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/=
29501026.287508/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjI=
tMTAtMjUvZWxvbi1tdXNrLXRlbGxzLWRlYnQtYmFua2Vycy1oZS1wbGFucy10by1jbG9zZS10d2=
l0dGVyLWRlYWwtb24tZnJpZGF5LXR3dHI_Y21waWQ9QkJEMTAyNjIyX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX=
21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjIxMDI2JnV0bV9j=
YW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB1be84cde" itemprop=3D"Sto=
ryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; =
text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-c=
olor: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> exactl=
y as long as possible</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Elon Musk yesterday pledged to close the acqui=
sition of Twitter Inc. by Friday in a video conference call with bankers he=
lping fund the deal, according to people with knowledge of the matter, Bloo=
mberg News reports.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The banks, which are providing $13 billion of =
debt financing, have finished putting together the final credit agreement a=
nd are in the process of signing the documentation, one of the last steps b=
efore actually sending the cash to Musk, said the people.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The Wall Street lenders, led by Morgan Stanley=
, had already been preparing in recent weeks to fund the debt, Bloomberg pr=
eviously reported. But nothing is ever certain with Musk, the mercurial bil=
lionaire who only weeks ago was seeking to back out of the deal. These late=
st developments suggest he is in the final stages of closing the transactio=
n by a court-issued Oct. 28 deadline.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The banks are expected to receive one of the l=
ast formalities -- a borrowing notice -- on Tuesday, and the cash is expect=
ed to be held in escrow on Thursday, the people said.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Is this deal going to close on Thursday? Oh no=
, no no no. He=E2=80=99s got until 5 p.m. on Friday. A plausible time to cl=
ose would be 4:45 on Friday, possibly 4:20. Really 5:30 is not entirely off=
 the table; if they are all doing good amicable closing stuff at 4:59 Twitt=
er is not going to go running to the judge to complain about it being a few=
 minutes late.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-1" style=3D"col=
or: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; bo=
rder-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; backgroun=
d-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[1]</span>
</a>=C2=A0Why close on Thursday and take all the suspense out of it?=C2=A0<=
/p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Though, really, the suspense is pretty much ou=
t of it. The key sentence here is not =E2=80=9CElon Musk yesterday pledged =
to close the acquisition of Twitter Inc. by Friday=E2=80=9D but rather =E2=
=80=9CThe banks =E2=80=A6 are in the process of signing the documentation.=
=E2=80=9D The=C2=A0<em>main=C2=A0</em><a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomber=
gbusiness.com/click/29501026.287508/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGl=
uaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMTAtMDcvbWF0dC1sZXZpbmUtcy1tb25leS1zdHVmZi1lbG9uLW=
11c2staGFzLXRocmVlLXdlZWtzLXRvLWNoYW5nZS1oaXMtbWluZD9jbXBpZD1CQkQxMDI2MjJfT=
U9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVy=
bT0yMjEwMjYmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB8a1dcc=
54" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=
=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: =
1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-c=
olor: #ccc;"> source of suspense</a>, since Musk said he planned to close, =
is whether his banks would fund their $13 billion commitments.<a class=3D"f=
ootnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-2" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoratio=
n: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000;=
 border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: transparent !impor=
tant; display: inline-block;">
<span>[2]</span>
</a>=C2=A0I figured they would, but people had doubts, and Musk=E2=80=99s l=
awyers were a little bit coy about it. Could the banks have said something =
like =E2=80=9Cthe deal has been terminated=E2=80=9D or =E2=80=9Cthere was a=
 material adverse effect=E2=80=9D or =E2=80=9Cwait Twitter has bots=E2=80=
=9D and refused to fund? I mean, no, not really, but if they=C2=A0<em>were=
=C2=A0</em>going to do that it would have been before drafting and signing =
the credit agreements. The banks are in now.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Also:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On the call, Musk also promised to=
 help the banks market the debt to money managers after the deal closes, th=
e people said.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I am very much looking forward to reading thos=
e marketing documents. =E2=80=9CSure Twitter <em>was=C2=A0</em>a huge fraud=
, but now it=E2=80=99s great, so give me my money.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Still, there=E2=80=99s some ancillary suspense=
, like who <em>else=C2=A0</em>will kick in some money to pay part of Musk=
=E2=80=99s equity check. Here=E2=80=99s <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomb=
ergbusiness.com/click/29501026.287508/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZ=
XdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMTAtMjUvYmluYW5jZS1jZW8tc2F5cy1oZS10aGlua3MtaGUtbGwt=
c3RpY2std2l0aC1tdXNrLWluLXR3aXR0ZXItYmlkP2NtcGlkPUJCRDEwMjYyMl9NT05FWVNUVUZ=
GJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIyMTAyNi=
Z1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB1b70eebc" itempro=
p=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #=
000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-=
bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"=
>  one guy who=E2=80=99s a maybe</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Binance Holdings Ltd.=E2=80=99s chief executiv=
e officer said he thinks he will stick with Elon Musk=E2=80=99s proposed $4=
4 billion buyout of Twitter Inc. amid potential concerns from Washington ab=
out foreign investors backing the bid. =C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CI think so,=E2=80=9D Changpeng Zhao s=
aid when asked if he will stand by his financial commitment to Musk. Zhao s=
poke in Riyadh, Saudi Arabia, where he was attending the kingdom=E2=80=99s =
Future Investment Initiative conference on Tuesday.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusi=
ness.com/click/29501026.287508/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud3NqLmNvbS9hcnRpY2xlcy9zZXF1=
b2lhLWNhcGl0YWxzLXJvZWxvZi1ib3RoYS1wcmVkaWN0cy1zdWNjZXNzLWZvci1lbG9uLW11c2s=
tYXQtdHdpdHRlci0xMTY2Njc0Nzg4OD9tb2Q9aHBfbGVhZF9wb3M0/607f07ceef4b8524a319a=
23cBa9815182" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_bla=
nk" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-botto=
m-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; bac=
kground-color: #ccc;">here=E2=80=99s a yes</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Roelof Botha, the head of Sequoia Capital, sai=
d he thinks there are large improvements to be made for Twitter Inc.=E2=80=
=99s current business and that Elon Musk=E2=80=99s takeover bid for the soc=
ial-media company will be a success.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Mr. Botha, speaking at The Wall Street Journal=
=E2=80=99s Tech Live conference, said he thought Twitter could find better =
ways to make money beyond advertising and improve its product. Sequoia has =
committed $800 million for the deal. The funding is set to come from Sequoi=
a=E2=80=99s main venture funds, its wealth management business called Herit=
age, and its crossover fund Sequoia Capital Global Equities. ...</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CElon has succeeded in many different =
industries,=E2=80=9D Mr. Botha said. =E2=80=9CHe=E2=80=99s an incredible fi=
rst-principles thinker.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Mr. Botha said Sequoia ran financial models an=
d spoke to current and former employees when examining the potential of the=
 Twitter deal. He said he had spoken to Mr. Musk about potential changes to=
 the Twitter business, including around payments integration, and believed =
that Mr. Musk could address issues around account verification, such as abu=
se and spam, and introduce new monetization strategies such as using subscr=
iptions.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The approach of some investors in evaluating t=
he deal has drawn significant attention.=C2=A0Marc Andreessen, the co-found=
er of venture firm Andreessen Horowitz, wrote to Mr. Musk in April that he =
was willing to commit $250 million for the Twitter deal, with =E2=80=9Cno a=
dditional work required,=E2=80=9D according to documents made public in the=
 recent Twitter-Musk lawsuit. Andreessen agreed to ultimately invest $400 m=
illion.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This is the difference between investing your =
own money and investing as a fiduciary for your fund=E2=80=99s limited part=
ners. Elon Musk, when he announced his plans to buy Twitter, <a href=3D"htt=
ps://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29501026.287508/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cu=
dGhldmVyZ2UuY29tLzIwMjIvNC8xNC8yMzAyNTM0My9lbG9uLW11c2stdHdpdHRlci10YWtlb3Z=
lci10ZWQtdGFsay1xdW90ZS1zdG9jay1idXlvdXQ/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB9f93d918"=
 itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"=
color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px;=
 border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color=
: #ccc;">said things like</a> =E2=80=9Cthis is not a way to sort of make mo=
ney=E2=80=9D and =E2=80=9Cyou don=E2=80=99t care about the economics at all=
=E2=80=9D; more recently <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com=
/click/29501026.287508/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVz=
LzIwMjItMTAtMTkvZWxvbi1tdXNrLXNheXMtaGUtcy1vYnZpb3VzbHktb3ZlcnBheWluZy1mb3I=
tdHdpdHRlcj9jbXBpZD1CQkQxMDI2MjJfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV=
9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMjEwMjYmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1Z=
mY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBcd0973e1" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"i=
temscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none =
!important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-=
bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> he said that</a> he is =E2=
=80=9Cobviously overpaying.=E2=80=9D That=E2=80=99s fine! He=E2=80=99s rich=
, he=E2=80=99s using his own money, and if he wants to overpay for Twitter =
because he enjoys tweeting or thinks it=E2=80=99s good for free speech or w=
hatever, that=E2=80=99s his business.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But Roelof Botha can=E2=80=99t go to his LPs a=
nd say =E2=80=9Coh we=E2=80=99re not in this deal to make money, we don=E2=
=80=99t care about the economics at all.=E2=80=9D It=E2=80=99s their money!=
 He has to say things like =E2=80=9Cwe ran financial models.=E2=80=9D Did t=
hey? Sure, probably. I have previously defended Musk=E2=80=99s co-investors=
=E2=80=99 somewhat lackadaisical approach to due diligence on this deal. <a=
 href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29501026.287508/aHR0=
cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMTAtMDMvZXZlcnl=
vbmUtd2FudGVkLXRvLWJ1eS10d2l0dGVyLXdpdGgtZWxvbj9jbXBpZD1CQkQxMDI2MjJfTU9ORV=
lTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yM=
jEwMjYmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBfd9d0404" i=
